  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an intent to make restitution by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust warranting a carceral sentence to maintain public confidence and deter future misconduct, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate and inconsistent with sentencing guidelines for a $25,000 fraud. Taking into account the mitigating factor of a clean record, a sentence of 6 months is deemed sufficient and appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
}
